OL,3,GUK long range forecast
OL,4,
OL,5,COutlook for Wed 22 Jul to Fri 31 Jul
OL,6,FMost places will be dry at first with
OL,7,Fsunny spells, especially in the south,
OL,8,Fwhile northern and northwestern areas
OL,9,Fsee more cloud and occasional patchy
OL,10,Frain or drizzle. Through the weekend
OL,11,Fand into next week, conditions become
OL,12,Fa little more changeable, with showers
OL,13,Fand some longer spells of rain
OL,14,Fincreasingly likely, mainly across
OL,15,Fnorthern parts of the UK. Further
OL,16,Fsouth, many places should stay drier
OL,17,Foverall with some good sunshine,
OL,18,Falthough a few showers cannot be ruled
OL,19,Fout. Towards the end of the period,
OL,20,Fconfidence becomes lower, but there
OL,21,Fare signs that more settled and drier
OL,22,Fconditions may return, particularly in
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,23,Fthe south. Winds will be mostly light
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
OL,24,For moderate, though occasionally fresh
OL,25,Fin the north, while temperatures are
OL,26,Fexpected to be near or above average,
FL,164,160,301,260,100,100
PN,16303
